text: Lin Ya-wen (born 14 June 1994) is a Taiwanese korfball player. He played in the Netherlands with in the Dutch Korfbal League, being the first Taiwanese korftball player in the Dutch league. He is a member of the Chinese Taipei korfball team. With the national team he won the silver medal at the 2022 World Games in Birmingham, Alabama. ==References== Category:1994 births Category:Living people Category:Taiwanese korfball players
